    "After this, we have the second layer fully connected, i.e., all neurons from the previous layer are directly related to the next one to generate general semantic information.",
    "Finally, we have an output layer for classification tasks that commonly has a softmax activation operator and an optimizer [38].The following Eq. 3 denotes this:Where: M l represents each of the feature maps.",
    "M l-1 i is the pre-feuture map layer, K l i is the kernel, b is the bias, * refers to convolution.The neural network we use in this paper is described in Figs. 3 and 4.",
    "The 1D convolutional layers (Conv1D) comprise a kernel of size 3, padding same, and a selu activation method.",
    "In the output of each set, we have a 1D maxpole and a dropout 0."
